<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model">
An <b>External_geometric_model</b> is a type of 3D <b>Geometric_model</b> whose content is provided in an external file.
<p>The set of items of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> contains only one element that shall be an <b>Axis_placement</b>.
This Axis_placement specifies the reference location and orientation with respect to which placement of the External_geometric_model in other Geometric_models shall be defined.
</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Attribute: SELF\Representation.items 
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.SELF\Representation.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.SELF\Representation.items">
the <b>Axis_placement</b> that defines the reference position or orientation of the External_geometric_model.
<note>
Most of times, the position is the origin point of the coordinate space and the orientation matrix is the identity matrix.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Attribute: external_file 
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.external_file"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.external_file">
the <b>Digital_file</b> that contains the external geometry information.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Where: WR1 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.wr:WR1">
the <b>External_geometric_model</b> shall be a 3D model.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Where: WR2 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.wr:WR2">
The <b>Representation_context</b> of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> shall be of kind 'external'.
<note>
Because the <b>External_geometric_model</b> entity is a subtype of <b>Geometric_model</b>, the <b>Representation_context</b> of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> is actually a <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b>.
</note>
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
